CatDescriptText: Miss Sonja Coleman, 234 Burrows Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think it justifiable for residents to "put the finger" (notify law enforcement officers) on rackets if they exist in their respective communities?" answer reads: "Yes, I think they should. I think that it is their duty if they want to keep the community clean of all rackets."
